        "content": "<p>I wrote some code which, in a convoluted way, returns \"true\" if a certain <code>MetaM</code> call works, and \"false\" if it throws an error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">try</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üê</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">metaprogram</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">pure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"n\">catch</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is there a shorter idiom for this?</p>",
